max and the mud puddle

Page 1

Text:
Max is a little dog.
He sees a big puddle.
It looks fun to jump in!

Illustration idea:
A small brown puppy looking at a shiny puddle after the rain, tail wagging.

Page 2

Text:
“Splash!” goes Max.
Mud flies everywhere!
Max is very wet now.

Illustration idea:
Max jumping into the puddle, muddy water splashing all around, his tongue out in joy.

Page 3

Text:
A bird laughs.
“Max, you are messy!” says the bird.
Max just wags his tail.

Illustration idea:
A cheerful bluebird on a branch laughing while Max smiles, covered in mud.

Page 4

Text:
Max rolls in the grass.
The sun feels warm.
He is happy and sleepy.

Illustration idea:
Max lying on green grass, drying off in the sunshine, eyes half closed.

Page 5

Text:
“Time for a bath!” says Mom.
Max runs fast!
He does not want a bath!

Illustration idea:
Max dashing away from a smiling woman holding a towel and a small tub of water.

Page 6

Text:
But Mom finds Max.
She washes him clean.
Now Max smells nice again!

Illustration idea:
Max sitting in a bubble bath, clean and happy, Mom drying him with a towel.